25|$|In 2012, the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas (BSP), {{the central}} bank of the Philippines, expects {{official}} <b>remittances</b> coursed through banks and agents to grow 5% over 2011 to US$21 billion, but official <b>remittances</b> are {{only a fraction of}} all <b>remittances.</b> <b>Remittances</b> by unofficial, including illegal, channels are estimated by the Asian Bankers Association to be 30 to 40% higher than the official BSP figure. In 2011, <b>remittances</b> were US$20.117 billion.|$|R
